	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><img src="../ubb/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Post" border="0"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Yeah screw remedy. I haven't memmed that spell in a LONG time. <br />
<br />
The best bet for casters is to cast Cel Heal/Elixer as soon as they start taking damage and then figure out what to do next based on how things are progressing. If you cast it at 2500 hpts, the spells do 900/1500 healing and gives you time to either divine light, or CH them depending on how much they're getting beat on. Simple fact is that if you can't get the mob off them in the time it takes a celestial spell to run its corse you're screwed anyway, or you'd be oom trying to chain remedy heal them.<br />
<br />
Resist gear is not all that important to clerics. Wear your best mana gear instead and just use the walls to shield you from AEs. I've been through the entire HoT area just about, and there are very few places that you can't use physical structures to shield you from AEs. If you're getting hit by AEs, MOVE. You don't need line of sight to heal, so just keep using group select to target your groups tank, and the assist off him to target the mob, then assist heal whoever the mob is attacking. SIMPLE.<br />
<br />
Only exception to the resist gear rule is the MT CHer. Not sure if HoT summons, I've always been group healer for the most part, but if they do, you would do well to have reist gear to help suck up some of the AEs.</font></p>
	
	<p></p>
	<p></p>
